title: For Sale:  Small Unit Tactics and Force on Force Training
postcontent:
In February 2018, we are running 2 x 6 day training packages, with some options within those 6 day events. See below.
Package 1: Saturday 17 – Thursday 22 February 2018.
Package 2: Saturday 24 February – Thursday 1 March 2018.
Classes take place on a large private ranch close to Brady, Texas. The ranch offers excellent training land. There is a comfortable hunting lodge at the ranch which is the main accommodation option of choice. This will be the fourth year in a row that we have run classes at this ranch. It is an excellent training venue.
The first package is divisible into 2, 4 or 6 day class options (some alumni prerequisites apply, see below). There are options for beginners and alumni.
The second package consists of a 4 day Direct Action / Combat Patrol class (CTT alumni only), and a 2 day Force on Force Team Tactics / Close Quarter Battle Course. These latter options can be attended by anyone, separate from the 4 Day Combat Patrol Class.
Max Velocity Tactical (MVT) has established a reputation on the leading edge of immersive, scenario based, tactical live fire and force on force training. At MVT we are dedicated to developing and training tactical excellence at the individual and team level, in order to better prepare you to defend yourself and others during life threatening situations. Max Velocity Tactical operates the Velocity Training Center (VTC) tactical and leadership training facility near to Romney, West Virginia.
Tactical classes specialize in the teaching of combat proven, adapted, legitimate light infantry / unconventional warfare tactics, techniques and procedures. MVT conducts training for Responsible Citizens and US Special Operations Forces.
TacGun is promoted by MVT as an adventure activity with clear benefits to personal and professional development. TacGun is the packaging of holistic tactical training, a fun and exciting adventure sport that people of all ages can enjoy and benefit from. MVT TacGun involves both training and competition events.
More info at TacGunTexas.com

postcontent: The 357 S&W Magnum (9×33mmR), or simply 357 Magnum, is a revolver cartridge with a 357-inch (9.07 mm) bullet diameter.This smith&wesson 357 Magnum cartridge was introduced in 1934, and its use has since become widespread. This cartridge started the "Magnum era" of handgun ammunition and it is also regarded by many as an excellent hunting, metallic silhouette and self-defense round. With proper loadings it can also be effective against large or dangerous game, such as bear and ungulates, howerever many consider the larger magnum calibers to be more appropriate such as the .500 Smith & Wesson, .50 Action Express, .44 Magnum, .454 Casull, .41 Magnum as well as other larger magnum rounds. Comparatively, the 357 Magnum has less energy than the larger magnum revolver loadings but is smaller in diameter with high velocity allowing for excellent penetration properties, It is a fine small- and medium-game round and is sufficient to hunt deer at reasonable ranges if suitable loadings are used by a competent marksman.
